# Vercel React Best Practices (v1.1 Example)

## Server Components First

Use server components as the default. Add `"use client"` only when browser APIs, event handlers, or local React state are required.

```tsx
// Server component (default)
export default async function Dashboard() {
  const data = await fetchMetrics();
  return <MetricsGrid data={data} />;
}
```

## Server Actions for Mutations

Use server actions for writes so mutation logic stays on the server and close to route behavior.

```tsx
"use server";

export async function createProject(formData: FormData) {
  const name = formData.get("name");
  await db.projects.create({ name });
  revalidatePath("/projects");
}
```

## Caching Strategy

Design intentionally around request deduplication, data caching, and route-level cache behavior so rendering work is reused whenever possible.
